Very nice selection of fresh foods but the price point is extremely high, even higher than Whole Foods. In particular, the prepared entrees are priced much higher than they need to be. For an example, a medium size piece of unremarkable grilled chicken breast is $9.98 which is ridiculous.  Whole Foods sold the same size medium chicken but grilled properly and very good pricing for $7 for 2 pieces.  I suggest that Plum Market revisit the pricing of their prepared entrees.  Also, the staff I encountered at the Plum Market in Old Town Chicago were not friendly, did not appear to like working with the public and were poor representatives for this company. In the prepared foods section, several people were waiting to be served as the staff member just stood there daydreaming—training seems to be lacking.  It seems that Plum has a difficult time attracting quality employees which is a sad commentary on their recruitment and hiring practices.  There is no excuse for this in view of the tremendous profits grocery stores are making during covid. What is Plum Market doing to give back to its customers? Nothing.

I guess I don’t fit in the demographic of what is considered friendly customers. I grabbed a bottle of scotch and was trying to do the rest of my grocery shopping and one of the staff just followed me throughout he whole store. Would have been nice if he were to offer to hold my bag by the way he was following me but he just followed me down every aisle until I finished checking out and literally left the store. I figured maybe the neighborhood of Old Town had their share of shoplifters so I didn’t really think anything of it, but as I was getting checked out the cashier had to take an alarm off the bottle of scotch I  had in my grocery bag so maybe the guy just didn’t like my face. I was wearing a bright orange hunter’s beanie and a tan Carhartt jacket, sweat pants, and Ugg boots, I guess that just screamed unsavory character. I ended up returning the bottle and went next door and bought one from them instead. If you want to follow me while I pick up soda water and milk by all means go ahead and follow me, but offer to carry my bag or something for me while you are obviously tailing me; after all, I am still a customer, or  at least I was. Maybe for future reference just put up a sign and tell me I’m not welcome. That would save both our time. I’d gladly walk over somewhere that  I’m welcome.

Go here for emergencies not on a regular basis..unless you have time to kill waiting to be checked and money to burn for food that is much less expensive in the inner city...Yes it's the Gold Coast..and Corp knows it..so they take your money and time thinking we all are Rockefellers...as to that girl at the express counter this morning 1/19/19 7:30 a.m Saturday..she shamed all of you at Corp for doing a job obviously management felt to inferior to do themselves.
